eader":true,"content":"Filling"},{"content":"Place cream cheese into mixing bowl and mix <b>30 sec\/speed 7<b> with aid of spatula. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula and mix a further <b>30 sec\/speed 7<b> with aid of spatula."},{"content":"Add sugar, sour cream, flour, lemon juice, vanilla and salt and mix <b>30 sec\/speed 7<b> with aid of spatula."},{"content":"Without measuring cup, mix <b>30 sec\/speed 5<b> while adding eggs and egg yolks one at a time through hole in mixing bowl lid. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula and mix a further <b>30 sec\/speed 5<b>."},{"content":"Pour cheesecake filling over prebaked crust. Let rest five minutes. Bake for 10 minutes (450°F), then reduce heat to 200°F and bake a further 1 hour and 45 minutes (200°F). Clean mixing bowl."},{"content":"Turn off oven, crack open oven door and allow to cool slowly for one hour."},{"content":"Run a thin knife around the edge of the pan to loosen cheesecake and allow to cool at room temperature (approx. 2 hr.). Refrigerate until fully set (approx. 4 hr. or overnight)."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Strawberry Topping"},{"content":"Place strawberries, lemon juice and sugar into mixing bowl and cook <b>4 min\/140°F\/\/speed 1<b>. Transfer to a bowl and refrigerate until chilled."},{"content":"Just before serving, remove outer ring of springform pan. Pour Strawberry Topping over cheesecake, slice and serve."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Store leftover cheesecake in the refrigerator.","New York Cheesecakes bake optimally in a conventional oven. If using a convection oven, turn the fan off if your oven allows it, otherwise turn fan to lowest setting. All ovens heat differently however, so if using a convection oven it is recommended to reduce the temperature by 25°F-30°F and bake per conventional recipe time."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","2h 30m","12 slices"]}